title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\NotificationEndpointGrpcSettings
name: NotificationEndpointGrpcSettings
description:
Represents a gRPC setting that describes one gRPC notification endpoint and the retry duration attempting to send notification to this endpoint.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.NotificationEndpointGrpcSettings

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.authority
params.description: Optional. If specified, this field is used to set the authority header by the sender of notifications. See https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7540#section-8.1.2.3

params.name: data.endpoint
params.description: Endpoint to which gRPC notifications are sent. This must be a valid gRPCLB DNS name.

params.name: data.payload_name
params.description: Optional. If specified, this field is used to populate the "name" field in gRPC requests.

params.name: data.resend_interval
params.description: Optional. This field is used to configure how often to send a full update of all non-healthy backends. If unspecified, full updates are not sent. If specified, must be in the range between 600 seconds to 3600 seconds. Nanos are disallowed.

params.name: data.retry_duration_sec
params.description: How much time (in seconds) is spent attempting notification retries until a successful response is received. Default is 30s. Limit is 20m (1200s). Must be a positive number.
